Photo: CFPÂ Nine great apes at the San Diego Zoo have been vaccinated against COVID-19 after some gorillas were infected.Four orangutans and five bonobos received COVID-19 injections in January and February, the zoo confirmed earlier this week.The vaccinations followed a January outbreak of COVID-19 at the zoo's Safari Park. Eight western lowland gorillas got the virus, probably by exposure to a zookeeper who tested positive for COVID-19, officials said.The gorillas' symptoms were mild and limited to coughing, congestion and fatigue. They have fully recovered, according to the zoo.